<!-- introduce -->
<div class="confi-w3l" id="hello">
	<div class="container">
		<h3>Hi....</h3>
		<p>It's my pleasure to introduce myself! Well, I am Anas and raised in Bangladesh.</p>
		<p>A random guy with a million dreams currently studying at NSU, Dhaka, Bangladesh. When it comes to me, I would say from my very childhood I was quite different from average boys and girls around. I used to be quiet, loved to stay within myself most of the time, loved to study, and I was a pretty good student with a decent academic background. As I was very calm, some of my teachers used to call me ‘Shanto’ meaning poise and tranquil. I used to speak little and just sit in somewhere at my home and read. I felt happy doing so. Okay, so reading so far you can easily understand that I am an introvert. I think people have some misconceptions about introverts and some dominant ones are like people think introverts are shy, arrogant and not that much mindful. These things are not true because introverts aren’t like this because of their intentions rather it’s a natural behavioral pattern of themselves. Introverts are not necessarily shy. People don’t try to get it because our society works in that way where outgoing people are mostly praised and celebrated. Introverts think more than they say, aware of something in depth than they express, understand more than they deliver. They try to do what they love without letting everyone know and just aimlessly bragging about it. Okay, it seems I am talking much about it. Whatever let’s talk about my family. I believe in this course of life, where I am now is all made possible by my family, my parents and siblings. I am very blessed to have <a href="https://www.facebook.com/fatheralwaysright/" title="Rubel Rana" target="_blank">Rubel</a> and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100004816594334/" title="Abdullah Al Mamun" target="_blank">Abdullah</a> as my elder and younger brother. Especially I would love to talk about my elder brother <a href="https://www.facebook.com/shohel.khan.948494/" title="Shohel Rana" target="_blank">Shohel</a> who is more like a friend rather than a sibling. A person with whom I can share everything without any hesitation. He is very supportive and always inspires a lot about what I do. To him I just want to say, “God bless you and your brother loves you!”. Not being great at making many friends, I have a couple of friends who are very special and very close to my heart. <a href="https://www.facebook.com/kausar.khan.54772/" title="Kausar Khan" target="_blank">Kausar</a> is one of them who is currently studying at East West University. We have so many similarities between us, many common interests like passion, goals in life, behavioral pattern, attitude and more. An individual who is very heartwarming and supportive, never fails to motivate and inspire me and make me feel good at bad times. A companion, a friend in need and after all a brother. In university, I feel very grateful to have <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Ahnafhxn/" title="Ahnaf Hasan" target="_blank">Hasan</a>, <a href="https://www.facebook.com/sara.abrukun/" title="Sara Abrukun Ahmed" target="_blank">Sara</a>, <a href="https://www.facebook.com/izrat.jahan.319/" title="Izrat IJ" target="_blank">Izrat</a>, <a href="https://www.facebook.com/nahian.siraj/" title="Nahian Siraj" target="_blank">Nahian</a>, <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Shishir335/" title="Mahbub Shishir" target="_blank">Shishir</a>, <a href="https://www.facebook.com/mh.khan07/" title="M.H. Khan Shimanto" target="_blank">Shimanto</a> and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/toffazzal.hossain.52/" title="Syed Tofazzal Hossain" target="_blank">Tofazzal</a> as some of my close friends. A guy who wants to do something different in life, love to chase goals and love to work towards them. I have a soft corner for work out and computer programming. These are the things that make me feel happy and accomplished. Staying fit and eating healthy is like a passion and madness. A homo sapiens with a vision to go far in life, trying to conquer everything that I am thriving for with the help of almighty, the most beneficent and the most merciful.</p>
	</div>
</div>
